superheroes.name: Spiderman
superheroes.biography: Peter Parker is a high school student who gains spider-like abilities after being bitten by a radioactive spider.

superheroes.name: Superman
superheroes.biography: Superman is an alien from the planet Krypton who fights for truth, justice, and the American way.

superheroes.name: Wonder Woman
superheroes.biography: Wonder Woman is an Amazonian princess and warrior with god-like abilities.

superheroes.name: Iron Man
superheroes.biography: Tony Stark is a genius inventor who created a powerful suit of armor to save his life and protect the world.

superheroes.name: Batman
superheroes.biography: Bruce Wayne is a billionaire playboy and philanthropist who fights crime as the Dark Knight in Gotham City.

superheroes.name: Captain America
superheroes.biography: Steve Rogers, a soldier from World War II, was enhanced to the peak of human physicality and became Captain America.

superheroes.name: Flash
superheroes.biography: Barry Allen is a forensic scientist who gains the ability to move at superhuman speeds.

superheroes.name: Hulk
superheroes.biography: Bruce Banner transforms into the Hulk when he is angered, gaining immense strength and invulnerability.

superheroes.name: Thor
superheroes.biography: Thor is the Norse God of Thunder, protector of Midgard, and wielding the powerful hammer Mjolnir.

superheroes.name: Black Widow
superheroes.biography: Natasha Romanoff is a former KGB agent and a key member of the Avengers, skilled in espionage and hand-to-hand combat.

superheroes.name: Green Lantern
superheroes.biography: Hal Jordan is a test pilot who becomes the Green Lantern, using the power of a magical ring to fight evil across the universe.

superheroes.name: Aquaman
superheroes.biography: Aquaman is the king of Atlantis and protector of the oceans, possessing abilities to control sea creatures and survive underwater.

superheroes.name: Black Panther
superheroes.biography: T'Challa is the king of Wakanda, a technologically advanced African nation, and a superhero known as Black Panther.

superheroes.name: Scarlet Witch
superheroes.biography: Wanda Maximoff is a powerful mutant with reality-warping abilities, and a member of the Avengers.

superheroes.name: Doctor Strange
superheroes.biography: Doctor Stephen Strange is a former surgeon who becomes the Sorcerer Supreme to protect Earth from mystical threats.

superheroes.name: Deadpool
superheroes.biography: Wade Wilson is a mercenary who, after an experiment, gains regenerative healing powers.

superheroes.name: Hawkeye
superheroes.biography: Clint Barton is a master archer and former SHIELD agent, known for his precision and agility.

superheroes.name: The Punisher
superheroes.biography: Frank Castle is a former Marine who wages war on crime after his family is killed.

superheroes.name: Green Arrow
superheroes.biography: Oliver Queen is a billionaire who becomes a vigilante archer, protecting Star City.

superheroes.name: Luke Cage
superheroes.biography: Luke Cage is a hero for hire with unbreakable skin and superhuman strength.

superheroes.name: Shazam
superheroes.biography: Billy Batson is a young boy who, by saying the word 'Shazam', transforms into the superhero Shazam.

superheroes.name: Silver Surfer
superheroes.biography: Norrin Radd was a young astronomer on the planet Zenn-La who becomes the Silver Surfer after pledging himself to Galactus.

superheroes.name: Storm
superheroes.biography: Ororo Munroe, also known as Storm, is a mutant who can manipulate the weather and is a member of the X-Men.

superheroes.name: Wolverine
superheroes.biography: Wolverine is a mutant with enhanced senses and a healing factor, and is known for his claws made of adamantium.

superheroes.name: Cyclops
superheroes.biography: Scott Summers is a mutant with the ability to shoot powerful optic blasts from his eyes.

superheroes.name: Professor X
superheroes.biography: Charles Xavier is a mutant with telepathic abilities and the founder of the X-Men.

superheroes.name: Beast
superheroes.biography: Henry McCoy is a mutant with superhuman strength, agility, and the ability to leap great distances.

superheroes.name: Rogue
superheroes.biography: Rogue is a mutant who can absorb the powers and memories of others by touch.

superheroes.name: Vision
superheroes.biography: Vision is an android created by Ultron, later becoming a key member of the Avengers.

superheroes.name: Ant-Man
superheroes.biography: Scott Lang is a former thief who becomes Ant-Man after taking up the mantle from Hank Pym.

superheroes.name: Black Canary
superheroes.biography: Dinah Lance, also known as Black Canary, is a skilled martial artist and has a sonic scream.

superheroes.name: Nightwing
superheroes.biography: Dick Grayson is the original Robin who later becomes Nightwing after parting ways with Batman.

superheroes.name: Batgirl
superheroes.biography: Barbara Gordon is the daughter of Gotham City’s police commissioner, who becomes Batgirl to fight crime alongside Batman.

superheroes.name: The Atom
superheroes.biography: Ray Palmer is a physicist who uses a suit to shrink his size while maintaining his full strength.

superheroes.name: Hawkwoman
superheroes.biography: Shiera Sanders is a reincarnation of the ancient Egyptian heroine Hawkwoman, possessing the ability to fly and enhanced strength.

superheroes.name: Jonah Hex
superheroes.biography: Jonah Hex is a bounty hunter in the Old West, known for his scarred face and brutal nature.

superheroes.name: Zatanna
superheroes.biography: Zatanna Zatara is a powerful magician who casts spells by speaking backwards.

superheroes.name: Dr. Fate
superheroes.biography: Dr. Fate is a powerful sorcerer who wears the Helmet of Nabu, granting him magical abilities.

superheroes.name: Mister Miracle
superheroes.biography: Scott Free is the world’s greatest escape artist, hailing from the planet New Genesis.

superheroes.name: Red Tornado
superheroes.biography: Red Tornado is a synthetic android hero with the ability to generate powerful windstorms.

superheroes.name: Hawkman
superheroes.biography: Carter Hall is the reincarnation of an ancient Egyptian prince, who becomes Hawkman, armed with advanced weaponry and flight.

superheroes.name: Captain Marvel (Carol Danvers)
superheroes.biography: Carol Danvers is a former Air Force officer who becomes Captain Marvel after being exposed to alien technology.

superheroes.name: Ghost Rider
superheroes.biography: Johnny Blaze is a stunt motorcyclist who becomes Ghost Rider after making a pact with the devil.

superheroes.name: Blade
superheroes.biography: Blade is a half-vampire, half-human vampire hunter who possesses many vampire-like abilities.

superheroes.name: Jessica Jones
superheroes.biography: Jessica Jones is a private investigator with superhuman strength and the ability to fly.

superheroes.name: Iron Fist
superheroes.biography: Danny Rand is a martial artist with the power of the Iron Fist, which gives him incredible strength and energy blasts.

superheroes.name: The Thing
superheroes.biography: Ben Grimm is a member of the Fantastic Four who possesses immense strength and a rocky, nearly indestructible body.

superheroes.name: Sue Storm
superheroes.biography: Sue Storm, also known as the Invisible Woman, is a founding member of the Fantastic Four, with the ability to turn invisible and create force fields.

superheroes.name: Reed Richards
superheroes.biography: Reed Richards is the leader of the Fantastic Four and is a brilliant scientist with the ability to stretch his body.

superheroes.name: Johnny Storm
superheroes.biography: Johnny Storm, also known as the Human Torch, has the ability to create and control fire.

superheroes.name: Jean Grey
superheroes.biography: Jean Grey is a powerful telepath and telekinetic, and a founding member of the X-Men.

superheroes.name: Nightcrawler
superheroes.biography: Nightcrawler is a teleporter and member of the X-Men with a demonic appearance but a kind heart.

superheroes.name: Gambit
superheroes.biography: Gambit is a skilled thief with the ability to charge objects, particularly playing cards, with explosive kinetic energy.

superheroes.name: Iceman
superheroes.biography: Iceman is a founding member of the X-Men who can generate and control ice.

superheroes.name: Shang-Chi
superheroes.biography: Shang-Chi is a martial artist known for his skill in hand-to-hand combat and his ability to defeat even the strongest opponents.

superheroes.name: Venom
superheroes.biography: Eddie Brock becomes Venom after bonding with an alien symbiote. He possesses enhanced strength and a variety of unique abilities.

superheroes.name: Daredevil
superheroes.biography: Matt Murdock is a blind lawyer by day and Daredevil by night, using his enhanced senses and combat skills to fight crime in Hell's Kitchen.
